Anonymous Sat 01 Jan 2022 01:15:02 No.44385121 Report

>>44380530
This >>44384333 raised some good questions about world-building. It'll help if you can throw a few hints out in general about the world they live in. If they have lives measured in the thousands of years, if they are powerful youkai, if their world is sort-of Japan, are they deities with their own shrine, are they just sort of local kitsune spirits, is this a world of the supernatural with magic & creatures of magic, or more "realistic" world ..?

Not to be a pest, but this sort of info will have impacts upon personalities, what their day-to-day lives are like.

Let us imagine they are young, maybe only 200 years old. They might inhabit a shrine where very few humans (and other creatures) worship/pay tribute. Do these sisters share a shrine? Perhaps one has a shrine and the other is just allowed to live nearby & visit. Are they "poor" in the types & total tribute they take in? Is sex a "tribute?" What do they/can they offer to the community in return? Shrine spirits can promote prosperity, fertility, or maybe something dark like revenge. How Japanese do you want to be about it? Could be a lot of research.

Can they expect to live 500 years? 3000 years? Is their mother or other family alive? Do they commune with an actual goddess? Kitsune are often deities themselves, sometimes they are servants of more powerful beings, or bound to service of a human or spirit against their will.

Total number of tails indicates power levels, up to nine (examples of eleven for a goddess exist). Three or more is pretty rare and quite powerful, especially for younger kitsune. Seven or nine tails is usually 1000 to 2000 years old.

Kitsune are known gender changers, they can be male or female at need or whim.
